sually distinguished from entries that can be activated.</font></font></li><li><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=+2>Objects in direct-interactive interfaces that currently cannot be accessed should be visually distinguished from objects that can be activated.</font></font></li><li><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=+2>The shape of the mouse symbol should indicate the action that will occur if the user clicks the mouse button. </font><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="advance-info-cursor.jpg"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0" alt="The linked image shows an assortment of different cursor shapes in the Macintosh operating system and the X-Windows widget set. This different shapes give advance information as to what will happen when the user clicks the mouse."></a></font><font size=+2> </font></font></li><li><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=+2>Submenus should be shown when the mouse moves over the superordinate items. </font><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="menu-hierarchical1.jpg"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0" alt="The linked image shows a hierarchical menu where the subordinate menu pops up when its item in the superordinate menu is touched by the mouse cursor."></a></font></font></font></li><li><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=+2>Required formats of keyboard entries should be indicated. </font><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="table-example2.jpg"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0" alt="The linked image shows a computer form where the required format of the entries is clearly indicated."></a></font></font></font></font><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">&nbsp;<font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><a href="flawed-error-msg.htm"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0"></a></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></li><li><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size=+2>Potential adverse side effects      of      actions should be pointed out if the user may not be aware of them<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="6">, </font>and the user<font face="Arial,Helvetica">'</font>spermission  be requested. </font><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font size="6" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="advance-info-long-duration.jpg"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0" alt="The linked image shows a warning that the indexing operation that the user requested is likely to take some while. The user is advised to perform the operation during the night and asked whether he or she wants to carry out the action nevertheless."></a> <font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><font face="Arial,Helvetica"><a href="24-windows.pdf"><img src="../../../Graphics%20Templates/Diamonds/Di-red.gif" width="11" height="11" border="0" alt="The linked image shows a warning that the indexing operation that the user requested is likely to take some while. The user is advised to perform the operation during the night and asked whether he or she wants to carry out the action nevertheless."></a></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></font></li></ul></body></html>